modules.description: This module defines matchers for HTTP methods and URL paths to implement access control rules. It supports operations like parsing string representations of matchers, converting matchers to strings, and checking whether a request matches an access rule. Use cases include enforcing fine-grained access policies for API endpoints based on method and path patterns.

This module implements access control logic by matching HTTP methods and URL paths against defined rules. It provides data types for representing method and path matchers, along with operations to parse, stringify, and evaluate these matchers against incoming requests. For example, it can check if a `GET` request to `/api/users/123` satisfies a rule allowing read access to user resources, or deny access to restricted endpoints based on pattern matching.
